# tkv2 — keyed list public API

Slice `tkv2-keyed-for`: public toolkit `forKeyed(items, key)(render)` builds a
`TkNode` and lowers through `forKeyedView` on the std/ui path.

[signal](std/ui/primitives.ssc)
[forKeyed](std/ui/reactive.ssc)
[lower](std/ui/lower.ssc)
[defaultTheme](std/ui/theme.ssc)
[text](std/ui/typography.ssc)

```scalascript
val rows = signal("rows", ["a", "b"])
// Interpreter fallback invokes the row callback from the primitive context; a
// captured local survives that delayed call, while an imported global may not.
val mkText = text
val tree = forKeyed(rows, (item: String) => item)((item: String) => mkText(item))
val view = lower(tree, defaultTheme)

println("keyed-for-built")
```
